            <h2>Refund policy</h2>
            <p class="text-justify">According to AirAsia Airlines <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/refund-policy.aspx">refund policy</a>, the refund will be made to the person in whose name the ticket appears or the person who has paid for the ticket. The refundable amount may bear Refunds, penalties, and fees will be governedby the rules mentioned on the ticket. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">Moreover, you will receive the refund in the original form of payment, i.e., payments made by credit card will be returned to the credit card account, and so on. </p>
            <h3>Frequently asked question</h3>
            <h3 class="text-justify">Who can receive a refund with AirAsia Airlines? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">If you have purchased the ticket, you are eligible to receive a refund. You must provide necessary documents confirming that you have paid for the ticket such as an invoice or credit card. However, if the person who paid for the ticket couldn’t collect a refund due to sickness or death, the refund will be issued to an immediate family member, subject to the person providing a death certificate or medical certificate. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">How can I cancel a flight ticket with AirAsia Airlines? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">If you wish to cancel the flight ticket, you may call the AirAsia Airlines customer care office and inform them about the cancellation. You may visit the official website of the airlines and cancel your flight ticket. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">Where can I make the request for a refund? By when can I expect it? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">In order to make a request for a refund, you can visit the official website of AirAsia Airlines and fill out the refund request form. If you paid for the ticket with credit card, you will receive refund within 7 business days. However, if you paid via check or cash, you will receive refund within 20 days. </p>
